members.member:
Pagination is rather cumbersome, so workarounds are used.
property is used both as data input for users and as output for displaying (base displays it). So, to modify data in between these actions (namely, apply sorting and pagination), we need the following:
field and property allow to discriminate whether change was internal or external.
When internal change is made, it means we have new table to display. It may contain only one page, so cannot be used for storing both full 'original' table and for output one. We use to store 'original' instead.
When external change happens, contains new, unsorted and un-paginated data. Therefore, should be reset, as it contains previous, now invalid table.
Internal calls to go here, so is properly set.
